answers.body_markdown:
Your `total_gp` and `num_of_grades` are both `int`. Division of two integers is an integral operation, resulting in an `int` (where the rounding occurs). This integer is then assigned to a `double` variable `gpa`, but the damage is done already — there is no way to recover the lost information.

You need to hint to the compiler that you want the floating-point division, by making sure at least one of the operands is of a floating-point type. Either of these will work:

    gpa = (double) total_gp/num_of_grades;
    gpa = total_gp/(double) num_of_grades;

